Create a class named let&#39;s say **Response.java** create one variable in it named **shipment**.It will look like this:

    public class Response {
        public Response() {}
        public Response(Flux&lt;Map&lt;String, List&lt;String&gt;&gt;&gt; shipment) {
            this.shipment = shipment;
        }
        
        private Flux&lt;Map&lt;String, List&lt;String&gt;&gt;&gt; shipment;

        public void setShipment(Flux&lt;Map&lt;String, List&lt;String&gt;&gt;&gt; shipment) {
            this.shipment = shipment;
        }

        public Flux&lt;Map&lt;String, List&lt;String&gt;&gt;&gt; getShipment(){
            return shipment;
        }
    }

After that add following line in your code.

    Response resp = new Response(values);
    return resp;

This will give you the exact JSON you are looking for.

Basically you should build and return `Mono&lt;Map&lt;Map&lt;String, List&lt;String&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;`

You&#39;re getting an array because you&#39;re returing `Flux` which means &quot;many elements&quot;

But since`Mono&lt;Map&lt;Map&lt;String, List&lt;String&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;` is not readable, it is better to create a dto class like this:

    @Data
    @AllArgsConstructor
    @NoArgsConstructor
    public class Response {
    
        @JsonUnwrapped
        private Shipment shipment;
    
        @Data
        @AllArgsConstructor
        @NoArgsConstructor
        public static class Shipment {
    
            private Map&lt;String, List&lt;String&gt;&gt; shipment;
        }
    }

Then you write your controller like this:

    public Mono&lt;Response&gt; getShipment(List&lt;String&gt; shipmentOrderNumbers) {
        final String apiUrl = &quot;/some-path&quot;;
        final String queryParam = &quot;some-query-param&quot;;

        ParameterizedTypeReference&lt;List&lt;String&gt;&gt; expectedType = new ParameterizedTypeReference&lt;List&lt;String&gt;&gt;() {};

        return Flux.fromIterable(shipmentOrderNumbers)
                .flatMap(orderNo -&gt; this.client.get()
                        .uri(uriBuilder -&gt; uriBuilder.path(apiUrl).queryParam(queryParam, orderNo).build())
                        .retrieve()
                        .bodyToMono(expectedType)
                        .map(product -&gt; Pair.of(orderNo, product)) // map list to pair of orderNo vs list
                )
                .collectMap(Pair::getFirst, Pair::getSecond) // collect pairs keys and values to map
                .map(Response.Shipment::new) 
                .map(Response::new);
    }

Note: I&#39;m using here `Pair` class to wrap key-value instead of using single-valued hashmap. This class is from `org.springframework.data.util` package

